State's motion for resentencing.
Original Transcript SENTENCING HEARING  (15 pages) commencing JULY 15, 2014 received and filed.
JusticePoint Pretrial Services Report received and filed.

Defendant Denzell T Harris in court with attorney John P. Marchan.  Tyrone Martin St Junior appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by counsel, the defendant and the court.The Court imposed the following sentence:
Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 4 YEARS consecutive to any other sentence.   Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 2 YEARS with credit for 5 days time served.  Defendant shall serve 2 YEARS on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program, but NOT the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court ordered that all appropriate costs, surcharges, restitution and special assessments be paid from up to 25% of all inmate funds and as a condition of Extended Supervision.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant.  The Court STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation to the State Department of Corrections for a period of 3 YEARS.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION & EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
- As a condition of probation, the Court ordered the defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction with good time credit.  Release privileges to apply for school and work under condition of ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.  Court does not object to electronic monitoring, but does object prior to commencement of the school semester.
- No new violations of law rising to the level of probable cause.
- Attend the following programs and/or assessments:  AODA.
- Cooperate with the Department of Corrections.
- Participate in Cognitive Intervention programs.
- Obtain/maintain employment.
- Obtain GED/HSED.
- Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. 
- Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. 
- No contact with Jill S., and/or  the residence at 1952 S. 71st St., West Allis, W.; and Michelle A.
- No contant with co-defendant Demarco Lucas.
- Court ordered restitution in the amount of $630.99 to Jill S., joint and several with case 14CF1292 Demarco Lucas.
- Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge.
- Pay supervision fees as determined by the Wisconsin Department of Corrections.
- Pay all costs, fees and assessments, any cash bail to apply.  Failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment.
- Court advised defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.
